<br>
The FACTS<br>
- we had three groups tonite, the majority being longtime RvRers.<br>
- with the exception of one &lt;my mistake&gt; all group leaders have been on enough raids to know how they are run.<br>
- Lorne from Seekers, the battle commander, didn't show up.<br>
- Belce took up the position as not to disappoint those who did.<br>
- Belce asked for my assistance, as he felt it was required and I have had alot of group RvR experience of late.<br>
<br>
The PART you will not like<br>
- if you want to do your own thing and get your RPs, don't come to an organized raid where you are to work as a team.  You got RP envy, do it on your own time and quit wasting mine and anyone else's who showed up to be a part of a team.  Unless you are a STEALTH character, your ass is to be with your group 100% of the time.<br>
<br>
- if you are a Group Leader, your NUMBER ONE responsiblity is conveying the messages to your group.  We can only have 20 people in a chat.  I put the stealthers in tonite, the lead group and the minstrels.  Your group is depending on you, if you can't cut it, there is no shame in telling me.  Some people are slower typers than others, and don't want the responsiblity and have told me so.  That is fine by me, I have no problem with that.<br>
<br>
- if you are a Group Leader, don't tell me who you are picking to put in your group.  I am telling you for a reason who is in your group.  Don't like it, I don't care unless you have SOUND reasoning as to why.  (i.e. Dulcette you have three minstrels in this group and no healers).<br>
<br>
- dont' trust the Raid/Battle Commander, then back out of doing it.  I don't need those who don't trust my judgement.<br>
Spend 10sp and go back home.<br>
<br>
- if you are a member of a group and your GL does something against what the orders are, SPEAK up immediately.  That's teamwork.<br>
<br>
- use /follow at ALL TIMES, except on Stealth players or the raid commander.<br>
<br>
- Group Leaders pick a MA immediately if not assigned for whole raid and make sure everyone has it hotkeyed.<br>
<br>
- Going on an RvR raid, print a map.<br>
<br>
- reform when you are told to and where.  The number one reason I called off tonites raid.  HERE IT IS....  I asked four times to meet on the West side of MF1 on south corner.  Belce then asked twice before one of the other groups moved to us.  Finally he repeated himself two more times, for me to watch one group charge down the hill along with other Albions toward the tower.  <br>
<br>
- Listen Listen Listen Listen Listen and then follow the orders.<br>
<br>
- don't tell me INC, don't chit chat in chat, be specific.....Middies INC from DC to MF1 in valley.  INC means nada to a Raid commander who is trying to save lives and get realm points as opposed to just getting RPs.<br>
*************************************<br>
<br>
Now you are all asking, what the hell is she going on about.<br>
<br>
These raids are to make us successful.  To get the most realm points collectively, with the least amount of deaths.  To make us a refined unit so we can take down a keep of our own someday and maybe even one day take a relic.  Isn't that why we are playing the game.  Now we can do it a  haphazard kind of why with a call to arms, or we can be a well-oiled machine.  <br>
I put MY personal gaming time and effort, into learning RvR and all the techniques and strategies, so that WE as a guild and possibly an alliance can learn from them.  I am fortunate that other guilds wish me in their groups and that is where I learn from.  I am NO LONGER wasting MY time and anyone elses who wants to work as a team, by running any more of these events. IT'S NOT worth it to me anymore, especially when you can't get people to follow a simple instruction.  I WILL run one group RvR excursions and will work my way up to two groups eventually, when I know we can work together.<br>
Please note...yes I MAKE MISTAKES.  I make bad calls.  I run us into perfect setups, BUT I am the one who comes forward to assist us all in a more successful gaming experience and I take FULL RESPONSIBILITY for when I screw up.  No one feels more shame, then when I make a bad call and we have TPW.<br>
<br>
Tonite was an embarrassment to both guilds and especially to the newbies who came out.  We are better than this, but tonite we didn't prove it.<br>
<br>
To those who it was their first time, I am truly sorry that I called the raid and left you hanging there.  If you knew me well, you would know how frustrated I had to be, to do that.  I actually had to go afk and go and sit down and calm down before I could come back and deal with my own group.  And to Worst, I owe you an apology.  This was your first big RvR raid and I shouldn't have had you as a Group Leader.  I have complete faith in your competency but what I forgot is that you hadn't had the exposure of a larger scale.  So hun, I am sorry for putting that on you without even asking.<br>
<br>
Love me, hate me, but what is said is a diplomatic truth to tonite's events, considering all that we know together and have learned.<br>
