<br>
No matter the scale, each member's actions are important and critical.  If you are in a group, your actions can keep that group alive or get it wiped out, no matter if it's a group of 2 or a group/raid of 200.  Your group depends on you.  Period.<br>
<br>
Everyone makes mistakes.  People get lost.  Look away from their screen for few seconds.  Miss a line in the chatbox.  It happens.  I lost my group once today b/c I reached over to pat my dog.  *shrug*  Mistakes happen.<br>
<br>
These RvR events are meant to be fun and even large scale ones <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> can</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be fun and fast-paced.  I stress <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> can</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> because it has a few perquisites.  And if they aren't met, very few if anyone has a good time.<br>
<br>
The most <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> fundamental</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> thing that each person in a group needs to do is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> L I S T E N</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  If you can not listen, can not subordinate your individual desires for the needs of the whole, *do not attend the raid* -- and while you're at it go solo or log the heck out of the game because you will be a liability in a exp group as well.  <br>
<br>
When you are part of an exp group, you have to work together, you have to be where you are supposed to be, you have to do your job efficiently.  What the hell makes anyone think they need to do any <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> less</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> when in RvR?  Especially when you aren't holding up 7 people but 3-4 times that?  <br>
<br>
Simple, common sense should dictate all of this.  If you are screwing around and get killed, SOMEbody has to find and rez you, while this happens, the raid force can not proceed.  They are stuck waiting for someone to rez you and rebuff you and YOU are less effective b/c you are rez sick.  Now while all this occurs, the other 20-odd people sit around getting frustrated and bored.  If you are not tasked with sheathed perimeter security or some other job and are outside of buff range of your healer YOU ARE NOT WHERE YOU BELONG (I know you guys don't do this kinda stuff exp hunting).  If you die, find your group once you get rezed and *get buffed again!*  If your healer/buffer dies, once they are rezed find your group once you get rezed and *get buffed again!*  You are part of your group's ability to survive, stay with them to protect them.  NEVER take the battle to the enemy unless a Charge is called -- ESPECIALLY AT A FORTIFICATION because your casters are ordered up on the walls -- because you will out-run your caster support and often your healers.  You wouldn't do this fighting mobs, why do it in RvR??<br>
<br>
All this stuff causes wasted time.  All of it contributes to the slow pace of events.  Slow-pace = less fun.  All of it is common sense that I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> know</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> every experienced player knows.<br>
<br>
What I found utterly unfathomable, however, was the complete lack of listening skills on the part of a large segment of the raid.  There is no reason an instruction should need to be repeated three times (let alone the number of time some instructions had to be repeated during this raid).  No reason why when we are trying to regroup that people should be <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> running away from the raid group to get that extra RP because someone thinks there might be someone behind that tower</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  There is absolutely no reason why another group moving through the area should cause ANY disturbance despite anything they say or yell since <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> all your instructions come from your group leader in /group</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> that they've gotten from the /chat group.  There is no excuse for non-stealthers getting killed outside the healing range of their healer when told to regroup.  And while we're at it, there is utterly *no* reason anyone *other* than the raid commander for *anyone* to issue an order to &quot;fall back,&quot; &quot;attack,&quot; or in fact do *anything* i the /chat channel but provide information in the battle situation -- this is 100x more critical when the raid is small enough to have most or all of it IN the /chat group...this just leads to confusion and frustration for everyone.<br>
<br>
In short:  There's just no excuse for holding up a raid just to get a damned realm point.<br>
<br>
Hidien felt bad enough about the problems to apologize to us for the behavior of some of the SoL members.  And I extend my sincere apologies to SoL for the behavior of some of the Dagger members and I know Belce and Haemish feel the same way.  <br>
